
Apologies for the inconvenience. Let's try another approach using the `html-docx-js` library:

```javascript
// Include the library in your HTML file
// <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/html-docx-js/0.5.0/html-docx.js"></script>

// Assuming your HTML content is stored in a variable named htmlContent

// Convert HTML to docx format
var docx = htmlDocx.asBlob(htmlContent);

// Create a link element
var link = document.createElement('a');

// Set the href attribute to a URL created from the blob
link.href = URL.createObjectURL(docx);

// Set the download attribute to specify the file name
link.download = 'exported_document.docx';

// Append the link to the document body
document.body.appendChild(link);

// Trigger a click event on the link to prompt download
link.click();

// Remove the link from the document body
document.body.removeChild(link);
```

This code should properly convert your HTML content to a `.docx` file without any errors upon opening. Make sure to include the `html-docx.js` library in your HTML file before using this code. Additionally, replace `htmlContent` with the variable containing your HTML content.
